---
import LandingLayout from "../../layouts/LandingLayout.astro";
---

<LandingLayout
	title="Walk"
	description="A request walks the lattice — middleware, validate, handler, response schema."
	slug="walk"
>
	<main id="main" class="lp-walk">
		<section class="hero" aria-label="Hero">
			<div class="hero-bg" aria-hidden="true"></div>
			<div class="hero-inner">
				<div class="hero-top">
					<div class="brand-mark">
						<img src="/favicon.svg" alt="" width="40" height="40">
						Routa
						<span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
					</div>
					<h1 class="headline">The lattice between route, schema, and runtime</h1>
					<p class="lede">
						Every request walks a typed graph: middleware, validation, handler, named outcome. No
						hidden framework magic — the path is the product.
					</p>
					<div class="cta-row">
						<a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://routa-ts.dev/docs/">Get started</a>
						<div class="cli" data-cmd="pnpm create routa-ts@latest">
							<span>$ pnpm create routa-ts@latest</span>
							<button type="button">Copy</button>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="trace-wrap">
					<ol class="trace" aria-label="Request walk">
						<li class="active">
							<span class="n">01 · middleware</span>
							<strong>Context enters the lattice</strong>
							<p>
								Typed middleware composes auth, tenants, and deps into
								<code class="mono">ctx</code>.
							</p>
						</li>
						<li class="active">
							<span class="n">02 · validate</span>
							<strong>Zod owns the edge</strong>
							<p>
								Params, query, and body are checked against the route contract before the handler
								runs.
							</p>
						</li>
						<li class="active">
							<span class="n">03 · handler</span>
							<strong>Your code, named outcomes</strong>
							<p>
								Return <code class="mono">{"{ type, data }"}</code> from the declared response map —
								not raw status codes.
							</p>
						</li>
						<li class="active">
							<span class="n">04 · response</span>
							<strong>Schema closes the loop</strong>
							<p>The outcome schema shapes the HTTP response and the OpenAPI projection.</p>
						</li>
					</ol>
					<span class="pulse-line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="section-inner">
				<p class="section-kicker">How it fits</p>
				<h2 class="section-title">Route = contract</h2>
				<p class="section-lede">
					The filesystem path is the API surface. Schemas interlock into the lattice; Hono runs
					underneath.
				</p>
				<div class="code-panel" style="margin-bottom: 2rem">
					<div class="code-panel__bar">
						<span>request → lattice → response</span><span>trace</span>
					</div>
					<pre><code><span class="cm">// Named outcome — not res.status(201)</span>
<span class="kw">return</span> {"{"}
  type: <span class="str">"success"</span>,
  data: user,
{"}"};</code></pre>
				</div>
				<ul class="pillars">
					<li>
						<strong>Filesystem routes</strong>
						<p>URL segments from folders. One route file per path.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Contracted I/O</strong>
						<p>Zod at the boundary; handlers stay application-owned.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>OpenAPI peer</strong>
						<p>The same walk projects to a spec you can check and scaffold.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>CLI before run</strong>
						<p>Validate the graph, then build, then start.</p>
					</li>
				</ul>
				<ul class="built-on" style="margin-top: 2rem">
					<li>Hono</li>
					<li>Zod</li>
					<li>OpenAPI</li>
					<li>TypeScript</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="v0-note">
					<strong>v0</strong>
					— RC-honest. Schema-first REST, not a fullstack meta-framework.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="close">
			<div class="close-inner">
				<div>
					<h2>Walk the docs</h2>
					<p>Concepts for routes, schemas, middleware, and OpenAPI.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="cta-row">
					<a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://routa-ts.dev/docs/">Documentation</a>
					<a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/landings/">All options</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</LandingLayout>
